<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">Journal</p>
<p></p>
<p class="head">Mackenzies River alias Rocky Mountain</p>
<p></p>
<p class="head">&#8211; 1800 &#8211; 1 &#8211;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 29<sup>th</sup> September 1800<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Early this morning departed from Athabasca for Mackenzies River, in company with Mess<sup>rs</sup> Porter, Steinbrucks &amp; Wentzel &#8211; with a Fleet of six canons to be distributed in the following manner, viz Two for Slave Lake, one for Martin Lake, &amp; Three for M<sup>c</sup>kenzie River &#8211; the latter are Manned with only Three Men which is really very weak on account of the lateness of the Season<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Their Loading consists of 7 Bales Goods<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 5 kegs Powder, 3 bags balls, 2 bags shot, 4 cases Guns, 6 cases Iron Works<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 1 case knives<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 2 kegs H Wines, &amp; 16 ale kettles, total 31 Trading pieces and 12 pieces Provissions, viz. 1½ keg sugar, ½ a bag flour<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> 2 Bales Meat &amp; 8 bags Pemican<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  S<sup>t</sup> Cirs canoe is really very bad &amp; makes much water, put once ashore to Gum the sid Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  M<sup>r</sup> Porter gave us the loan of Two of his Men, as his Canoes are Manned with 5 Men each &#8211; he had much trouble to make Bernier one of his Men consent to embark, the fellow at first possitively Refused, &amp; did not go untill M<sup>r</sup> Porter commanded another en payant in his place &#8211; he then went swearing the Devil might take him if he had stirred a Step.  <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Si il y avoit point desgages</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Encamped at Lanset.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 30<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>s soon as we arrive at the first Portage M<sup>r</sup> Porter's people took possesion of their 2 Men, nevertheless we encamped all together at the End of the Embarras, but too late to Gum S<sup>t</sup> Cirs Canoe<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p>Wednesday the 1<sup>st</sup> October.  Encamped after dark at the end of the last Portage &#8211; had very much trouble to get S<sup>t</sup> Cirs Canoe over the Portages without iniminent</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">danger</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[1]</span></p>

